neighborhood_overview: This unit is located in a very commuter friendly area. 20 minutes walking to McCormick place or a 5-7 minute bus ride. 3 -7 minute ride on the red line train to downtown. 15-20 minute walk to Soldier Field or Museum Campus. It has multiple options to explore the City of Chicago including taking the Chicago Water Taxi! The area is very lively and safe due to the many restaurants located walking distance from this unit. This neighborhood offers more things to do then the area located by McCormick Place. I have heard numerous guests say how close this is to the loop and the ample transportation options that are available here! I look forward to hosting you!
notes: The Uber to McCormick Place is less than $3 dollars, if you get dropped off a block away from the center itself. Best intersection is Calumet and 21st.

neighborhood_overview: My place is located in the middle of Armour Square Chicago.   The neighborhood is safe and the neighbors are cordial.  Armour Square's most recognizable landmarks are the historic Armour Square Park and nearby Guaranteed Rate Field, which sits at the southeast corner of W. 35th and Shields Avenue, on the neighborhood's southern most end. Guaranteed Rate is home to the Major League Baseball franchise, the Chicago White Sox.  Armour Square is located just south of Downtown/Loop/Chinatown.
transit: My place is about a five minute walk to the 24 Bus stop, located on 26th St. and Wentworth Avenue.  The northbound 24 Bus will take you through Chinatown to the Redline train, or if you stay on the 24 Bus, it will take you through the loop and downtown.  From the Redline train you are able to pretty much navigate the entire city on the same line or through transfer to other lines. I am happy to give directions as needed.  Please do not hesitate to contact me.
access: Guests have access to the entire unit.
interaction: I am available by phone call and text.
house_rules: Please limit noise after 10:00 pm. Absolutely no parties or gatherings are allowed.

From May to September there is a water taxi that goes up the river from Chinatown to Michigan Avenue and the lake.
notes: I have a lovely, quiet, gentle  and hypoallergenic poodle. She is very friendly and loves seeing people. There is plenty of free 24 hr. street parking, but no parking available in the garage.
transit: Great location with the easiest public transportation and Divvy bike rental within one block radius.  No onsite parking is available, but there is plenty of free, safe, street parking around the building.  From O'Hare, you can take the CTA Blue Line, change to Red Line and then a 7 minute walk. Depending on time of day, uber or taxi is also an option.  The 62 bus will take you downtown, it stops right downstairs from the loft.  The 21 bus goes to McCormick Center, it stops one block away on Cermak.  CTA Red Line is a 7 minute walk; you can connect to the Blue Line to get to O'Hare airport.  CTA Orange Line and #62 bus take you to and from Midway airport.  I recommend (Hidden by Airbnb) maps for most accurate navigation of transportation around the city.

summary: An exceptional experience within a wonderful 2nd floor apartment located in Chicago's Chinatown, less than 20 minutes away from the loop by train or bus. description: An exceptional experience within a wonderful 2nd floor apartment located in Chicago's Chinatown, less than 20 minutes away from the loop by train or bus. You get a private bedroom with a closet, hangers, iron and a full size bed ideal for two but has worked for three small persons. I also have a twin mattress available for a third person.  The apartment has a modern open layout with a combined dinning room and living room. The apartment features pieces from my favorite artists and photos from around the world. Guests will be able to make use of the kitchen, bathroom and dining space in addition to the bedroom. I'll be available to answer any questions you may have about the city while you're around.  If you need
neighborhood_overview: Just two blocks from Wentworth (one of the main strips in Chinatown) you'll have easy access to plenty of delicious dinning options. Duck, Dim Sum, Hot Pot/Steamboat,  Noodles, Bakeries, Tea cafes, Dessert cafes, Korean and Vietnamese are some of the many options. There is also a taco stand and the best sandwich in the world (according to USA Today 2015) right across the highway.  There are a couple of museums in the neighborhood one dedicated to the History of Chinatown and the other to Asian art. Various gift shops can be found as well as small Chinese grocery stores. There is western pharmacy down the street as well if you need to get western snack or easy foods as well.  The are some lovely parks to walk around, one to note is Ping Tom park where you can get a great view of the skyline and during the summer months also has a water taxi to downtown. If you're lucky you might also catch a movie or live band.
notes: You are renting the guestroom in my apartment. The bedroom is ideal for two persons but it is available for three if you are looking for a budget friendly accommodation. I've had several very positive experiences with this option so I keep offering it. I prefer to greet my guests in person but if I'm at work or head to bed early I leave key for my guests in a key safe outside the building.
transit: The Red Line train is the easiest way to get around the city, but there are plenty of buses to take you to McCormick Place, the Loop, Bridgeport or Pilsen.  The apartment is also close to several highways and there is free neighborhood parking in the streets a half block away. You can reach the Cermak/Chinatown MRT/ Rail station in 5 minutes which will take you to the loop in less than 10.  The neighborhood is also in between McCormick Place convention center and the trendy Pilsen and Bridgeport neighborhoods. Uber can get you to either destination in about 5 minutes. You can walk to McCormick Place in about half an hour.
access: Guests will be able to make use of the kitchen, bathroom and dining space in addition to the bedroom.
interaction: I'll be available to answer any questions you may have about the city while you're around.  If you need a quiet space to come to after a long day of work, touring around the city, or raging at a festival,  you'll have no problem here.  I've also had the pleasure of sharing meals, drinks and dances with some of guests, I'll have no problem helping you get the most out of your time in Chicago.
house_rules: • Check-in time is after 3pm. Shoes off inside the apartment Smoking must be done outside Lock all the locks when leaving or entering  Don't leave a mess  Enjoy yourself

Chicago native, currently working at the airport and traveling whenever possible.

Photography - I was a portrait photographer for several years.

Travel

While staying in my apartment I'll be happy to answer any questions you may have about the city and give you recommendations about where to go in case you need help.

neighborhood_overview: The neighbor is a tree-lined residential neighborhood with local bars and restaurants central to everything. 31st and 35th street are in walking distance. Both streets lead to the gorgeous Lakeshore Drive beachfront bike path. Before you go, try some of the city’s best Italian Ice at Ferro’s on the corner of 31st and Wentworth. Or how about a delicious funnel cake from the Sugar Shack on 26th Street?  Chinatown offers a variety of oriental food, shopping, and entertainment options. Sox Stadium on 35th St. offers games, restaurant with full bar, merchandise, and more. It gets a little congested on games days but that’s no problem for you because you’re in walking distance. The Red Line train on 35th is $2.25 takes you into downtown in 10 mins. Chicago has so much variety of activities. Please feel free to ask me for ideas! McCormick Place, Wintrust Arena, and Marriott Marquis all a quick 10 minute drive from the home.
transit: If you are going downtown I suggest taking an Uber or public transportation. Parking downtown is a headache and expensive. Other than downtown and rush hour traffic, driving in the city is fairly easy from where you are staying.

neighborhood_overview: We are in Chinatown, just south of the South Loop, the gateway into downtown, and where most major outdoor events take place whether in the Parks or in Soldier Field. If food is your scene (and we all love to eat!) Chinatown is the largest Asian neighbourhood in the city with foods ranging from Bubble Tea and Dim Sum to Haute Seafood Asian Fusion! A little known secret for Seafood in Chicago is that Chinatown is THE place to get the Freshest and Live Seafood in the city. And for the best value too! Just a minute away in the adjacent neighbourhood of Pilsen you have artists galleries up and down Halsted St and a lovely Brewery (Moody Tongue) with a Fantastic Tasting Room. And of course just a minute to the north is The South Loop which is host to numerous World Class Museums, Soldier Field, and The Parks which hold all the Major Outdoor Events like Lollapalooza, The Blues Festival, and The Taste of Chicago!
notes: -Noise Warning- Because our building is centrally located on major cross streets and railways, and near the Chinatown Fire Station, you can some times hear the hustle of the City.  Of course you'll be in the thick of Chinese Culture, so some times you may see practices from rural Asia, like curing meats and fish outside to drying fruits and peanuts in the sun. But it's all in good fun! We use hypo-allergenic linens.   We want to make sure that your stay exceeds your expectations... When making a request, please tell us a little about yourselves, your interest in our home and indicate that you have read the full listing and house rules... Thank you!
transit: Our Condo comes with 1 dedicated Parking Spot with plenty of free parking just around the corner. Chinatown has very quick, easy access to Major Highways, and Public Transportation taking you to major destinations within minutes. Also very close by is an entrance to Lake Shore Drive which can take you up the famous and scenic city coastline or down to Hyde Park where U of C is located and The Museum of Science and Industry. Just a couple blocks away in the heart of Chinatown are the Red and Green Line Trains that can take you to every Major destinations downtown within minutes!
access: Guests will have access to everything aside from a storage closet and a secondary exit which isn't really used by anyone in the building.
interaction: We like to meet and welcome our guests. We're foodies and are in the food industry so we'll be happy to give you our recommendations in the city!
house_rules: - NO PARTIES - No smoking.  - Please respect the neighbourhood and our neighbours by not being loud or littering outside the home. We are friends with our neighbours and value our relationships with them.  - No unregistered guests allowed.  - Please take shoes off inside, it's just hygienic. ~Breaking of the rules will result in the forfeiture of the deposit.
host_about: We're newly weds wanting to begin an adventure together. We love to travel, and eat, and eat more, and then go into food coma.

neighborhood_overview: We are in Chinatown, just south of the South Loop, the gateway into downtown, and where most major outdoor events take place whether in the Parks or in Soldier Field. If food is your scene (and we all love to eat!) Chinatown is the largest Asian neighbourhood in the city with foods ranging from Bubble Tea and Dim Sum to Haute Seafood Asian Fusion! A little known secret for Seafood in Chicago is that Chinatown is THE place to get the Freshest and Live Seafood in the city. And for the best value too! Just a minute away in the adjacent neighbourhood of Pilsen you have artists galleries up and down Halsted St and a lovely Brewery (Moody Tongue) with a Fantastic Tasting Room. And of course just a minute to the north is The South Loop which is host to numerous World Class Museums, Soldier Field, and The Parks which hold all the Major Outdoor Events like Lollapalooza, The Blues Festival, and The Taste of Chicago!
notes: Because the buildings are centrally located on major cross streets and railways, and near the Chinatown Fire Station, you can some times hear the hustle of the City. Of course you'll be in the thick of Chinese Culture, so some times you may see practices from rural Asia, like curing meats and fish outside to drying fruits and peanuts in the sun. But it's all in good fun! We use hypo-allergenic linens. We want to make sure that your stay exceeds your expectations... When making a request, please tell us a little about yourselves, your interest in our home and indicate that you have read the full listing and house rules... Thank you!
transit: Our Condos come with a dedicated Packing Spot each, 2 total, with plenty of free parking just around the corner. Chinatown has very quick, easy access to Major Highways, and Public Transportation taking you to major destinations within minutes. Also very close by is an entrance to Lake Shore Drive which can take you up the famous and scenic city coastline or down to Hyde Park where U of C is located and The Museum of Science and Industry. Just a couple blocks away in the heart of Chinatown are the Red and Green Line Trains that can take you to every Major destinations downtown within minutes!
access: Guests will have access to everything aside from a storage closet and a secondary exit which isn't really used by anyone in either building.
interaction: We like to meet and welcome our guests. We're foodies and are in the food industry so we'll be happy to give you our recommendations in the city!
house_rules: - - NO PARTIES - - No smoking.  - - Please respect the neighbourhood and our neighbours by not being loud or littering outside the home. We are friends with our neighbours and value our relationships with them.  - - No unregistered guests allowed.  - - Please take shoes off inside, it's just hygienic. - ~Breaking of the rules will result in the forfeiture of the deposit.
host_about: We're newly weds wanting to begin an adventure together. We love to travel, and eat, and eat more, and then go into food coma.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is fairly quiet. However, we are in a major city, so expect some road noise, occasional siren, etc. Not an overly dangerous area, just use your travel common sense, be polite, and don't wander about during ridiculous, and you should be fine here!
notes: We do have furry friends in our home, an 8-year-old, well-trained golden retriever who works as a service and therapy dog and is very friendly, but well-behaved.  We also have a kitten.  They can be shut away in our private space for the duration of your stay if needed, but those who are definitely allergic to dogs and/or cats may want to reconsider this option!
transit: We are steps from Red and Green Line stops, as well as a Divvy (rental bike) rack, and you can catch the water taxi about a block away.  Bring your car and park on the street for free and without a permit. Alternatively, utilize Uber and/or Lyft for a no-hassle ride. There is also lots (including soldier field) within walking distance!

interaction: Need help, recommendations, maps, etc? Just ask! Contact us ahead of time for special requests. THERE ARE LOTS OF EXTRAS AVAILABLE HERE for an additional fees, as requested by each guest.  There are bikes for rent, breakfast can be ordered most days (bed and breakfast style!), reserve a bottle of wine or champagne for after a day of sight-seeing, set up pick-up/drop-off from the airport or train station, request dry-cleaning or laundry service for an easy vacation, two high-school babysitters on the premises can be reserved for an adult date night, and more!  Need a Ventra/Transit card to get around the city by public transportation, we keep a few on hand (you can add money through the host!) in addition to bus and rail maps, so you can hit the ground running when you arrive in the city! Let us know what we can do to make your stay a great one...
house_rules: - Generally, we observe quiet hours between 10 pm and 8 am (it's ok to shower and make your breakfast, but no TV, loud conversations, etc.). If you need to come in late, not a problem with advanced notice so we don't hit you with a baseball bat ;)  Feel free to utilize the kitchen to prepare meals. However, please clean up your dishes etc. Let us know of any special requests ahead of time. We can accomodate a family, if children etc. are willing to sleep on an air mattress or cot during their visit. Pets MAY be welcome with prior authorization from your host.  Common spaces are available for use, but all areas above the second floor are off limits to guests without host’s permission. Laundry room is available for use, drop $1 in the jar per wash/dry (honor system) to offset supplies/utilities. A PHOTOGRAPH OF THE BOOKING GUEST'S GOVERNMENT ISSUED ID CARD WILL BE TAKEN AT CHECK-IN IN EXCHANGE FOR KEYS TO ACCESS THE PROPERTY.  We're pretty easy going, if you're not sure...just ask!
host_about: Hello, we are a laid-back, family of three.  Having lived abroad ourselves, we are very social, and enjoy meeting new people.  I work from home full-time (with my trusted golden retriever, Zoey, for company) while my two kiddos attend high school here in the city.  We truly enjoy living in Chicago, and love to share our favorite spots and tourist tips with visitors!

neighborhood_overview: We are in Chinatown, just south of the South Loop, the gateway into downtown, and where most major outdoor events take place whether in the Parks or in Soldier Field. If food is your scene (and we all love to eat!) Chinatown is the largest Asian neighbourhood in the city with foods ranging from Bubble Tea and Dim Sum to Haute Seafood Asian Fusion! A little known secret for Seafood in Chicago is that Chinatown is THE place to get the Freshest and Live Seafood in the city. And for the best value too! Just a minute away in the adjacent neighbourhood of Pilsen you have artists galleries up and down Halsted St and a lovely Brewery (Moody Tongue) with a Fantastic Tasting Room. And of course just a minute to the north is The South Loop which is host to numerous World Class Museums, Soldier Field, and The Parks which hold all the Major Outdoor Events like Lollapalooza, The Blues Festival, and The Taste of Chicago!
notes: Because our building is centrally located on major cross streets and railways, and near the Chinatown Fire Station, you can some times hear the hustle of the City. Of course you'll be in the thick of Chinese Culture, so some times you may see practices from rural Asia, like curing meats and fish outside to drying fruits and peanuts in the sun. But it's all in good fun! We use hypo-allergenic linens. We want to make sure that your stay exceeds your expectations... When making a request, please tell us a little about yourselves, your interest in our home and indicate that you have read the full listing and house rules... Thank you!
transit: Our Condo comes with a dedicated Parking Spot with plenty of free parking just around the corner. Chinatown has very quick, easy access to Major Highways, and Public Transportation taking you to major destinations within minutes. Also very close by is an entrance to Lake Shore Drive which can take you up the famous and scenic city coastline or down to Hyde Park where U of C is located and The Museum of Science and Industry. Just a couple blocks away in the heart of Chinatown are the Red and Green Line Trains that can take you to every Major destinations downtown within minutes!
access: Guests will have access to everything aside from a storage closet and a secondary exit which isn't really used by anyone in the building.
interaction: We like to meet and welcome our guests. We're foodies and are in the food industry so we'll be happy to give you our recommendations in the city!
house_rules: - - NO PARTIES - - No smoking.  - - Please respect the neighbourhood and our neighbours by not being loud or littering outside the home. We are friends with our neighbours and value our relationships with them.  - - No unregistered guests allowed.  - - Please take shoes off inside, it's just hygienic. - ~Breaking of the rules will result in the forfeiture of the deposit.
host_about: We're newly weds wanting to begin an adventure together. We love to travel, and eat, and eat more, and then go into food coma.

neighborhood_overview: We are in Chinatown, just south of the South Loop, the gateway into downtown, and where most major outdoor events take place whether in the Parks or in Soldier Field. If food is your scene (and we all love to eat!) Chinatown is the largest Asian neighbourhood in the city with foods ranging from Bubble Tea and Dim Sum to Haute Seafood Asian Fusion! A little known secret for Seafood in Chicago is that Chinatown is THE place to get the Freshest and Live Seafood in the city. And for the best value too! Just a minute away in the adjacent neighbourhood of Pilsen you have artists galleries up and down Halsted St and a lovely Brewery (Moody Tongue) with a Fantastic Tasting Room. And of course just a minute to the north is The South Loop which is host to numerous World Class Museums, Soldier Field, and The Parks which hold all the Major Outdoor Events like Lollapalooza, The Blues Festival, and The Taste of Chicago!
notes: Our home is in a very quiet residential area directly behind the main Chinatown Mall.  Of course you'll be in the thick of Chinese Culture, so some times you may see practices from rural Asia, like curing meats and fish outside to drying fruits and peanuts in the sun. But it's all in good fun!   We want to make sure that your stay exceeds your expectations... When making a request, please tell us a little about yourselves, your interest in our home and indicate that you have read the full listing and house rules... Thank you!
transit: Our Home comes with 1 dedicated Parking Spot with free street parking just around the corner. There is also paid parking and the Chinatown Parking Lot is a few blocks away. Chinatown has very quick, easy access to Major Highways, and Public Transportation taking you to major destinations within minutes. Also very close by is an entrance to Lake Shore Drive which can take you up the famous and scenic city coastline or down to Hyde Park where U of C is located and The Museum of Science and Industry. Just a couple blocks away in the heart of Chinatown are the Red and Green Line Trains that can take you to every Major destinations downtown within minutes!

Downtown is pretty close and all the main attractions of the city! The neighborhood is pretty safe , you will have a Walgreens just one block away! A ton of restaurant in front of the building! notes: This is a duplex condo with three rooms and two bathrooms, the place is shared with other Airbnb guests ! In the first flat you will find: 1 bathroom, kitchen and living room. In the second flat there are the bedrooms and the other bathroom. There are stairs from the first flat to the second flat. The entrance of the building is a common entrance with the best chinese restaurant in the city. It’s good because you don’t have to walk too much to reach the restaurant. In the other hand, only the entrance and hallway smell a lot like food because of the restaurant but once you’re inside the apartment there is no food smell at all. Our neighbors are traditional Chinese people and they use to hang their clothes in their area so you may see that before get in the house. Inside the house everything is tidy and clean!

neighborhood_overview: Chinatown Chicago’s Chinatown is one of the largest neighborhoods of its kind in the US. Located on the city’s near South Side, the vibrant and energetic culture is reflected in the area’s many specialty shops, cultural cuisine and signature landmarks, like Ping Tom Memorial Park and a Buddhist Temple. The main drag of Wentworth Avenue is a dim sum drenched display of Chinese food perfection. Along this epic street, you will discover restaurants, distinctive boutique shopping and the Chinatown Gate, a beautifully ornamented entryway to the neighborhood. Just north of the Wentworth Avenue District is Chinatown Square, the largest Chinese mall in the Midwest. Besides hosting top restaurants, like Ken Kee, Phoenix or Lao Sze Chuan, you will find an incredible collection of public art that includes zodiac-inspired animal sculptures and twin pagodas. neighborhood_overview: This is the best location ever! Few places have a train that works 24/7 less than a block away! This is one!(Chinatown Red Line). Downtown is pretty close and all the main attractions of the city! The neighborhood is pretty safe , you will have a Walgreens just one block away! A ton of restaurant in front of the building! You will have a Divvy Bike station just one block away and few blocks away is the Chinatown Water Taxi Station that will take you over the river into Downtown for just 5$! Also there is a bus that takes you straight to downtown just in front of the building!
notes: This is a duplex condo with three rooms and two bathrooms, the place is shared with other Airbnb guests ! In the first flat you will find: 1 bathroom, kitchen and living room. In the second flat there are the bedrooms and the other bathroom. There are stairs from the first flat to the second flat. The entrance of the building is a common entrance with the best chinese restaurant in the city. It’s good because you don’t have to walk too much to reach the restaurant. In the other hand, only the entrance and hallway smell a lot like food because of the restaurant but once you’re inside the apartment there is no food smell at all. Our neighbors are traditional Chinese people and they use to hang their clothes in their area so you may see that before get in the house. Inside the house everything is tidy and clean! This room has a good size for a full bed, if you are three people we can add an extra air mattress with no extra fees, but the room will become very small. This is a good option i
transit: *Grant Park: just 10 min by public transportation. *Whithe Sox Field: just 14 min by public transportation. *McCormick Place: just 14 min by public transportation. *Illinois Medical District: 12 min by car - 26 min by public transportation. *United Center: 13 min by car - 30 min by public transportation.
access: You can use the kitchen, oven, pan, pots, plates, coffee maker, etc! Also two bathrooms, living room, hair dryer, iron! You will have WiFi, clean towels, sheets, comforter, Shampoo (2in1), hand’s soap, body’s soap, toilet paper.
interaction: If you text me I will be there for you most of the time I’ll try to give you quick responses! If you are a tourist I will love to tell you about some places you can’t miss!
house_rules: 1. If you use the kitchen, microwave, oven, plates, pans, pots, glasses, cups, kitchen table, living room table, coffee maker, fridge, etc.. you have to leave it clean!  2. If you take a bath you have to clean the hair you leave. 3. Don’t sleep with decorative pillow 4. You should avoid be noisy, specially after 9pm. 5. You Have to lock the entrance door once you get in the house or left the house! 6. You have to leave the keys in the right place after checkout ! (In the lockbox)  7. If you broken/lost/damage the keybox, lock or keys you will have to pay for it!  8. Don’t take plates, glasses, forks, pans, pots, etc, to your room!  9. You can’t bring pets! 10. You can’t smoke inside the house. 11. You can’t bring people to sleep over if they aren’t in your reservation or if you don’t notify me.
